.SH NAME
EXT_texture_compression_rgtc \- EXT_texture_compression_rgtc extension
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]EXT_texture_compression_rgtc\f[R] extension is part of the
WebGL API and exposes 4 RGTC compressed texture formats.
RGTC is a block\-based texture compression format suited for unsigned
and signed red and red\-green textures (\f[B]R\f[R]ed\-\f[B]G\f[R]reen
\f[B]T\f[R]exture \f[B]C\f[R]ompression).
.PP
WebGL extensions are available using the
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext.getExtension()\f[R] method.
For more information, see also Using Extensions in the WebGL tutorial.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] Support depends on the system\[cq]s graphics driver.
There is no support on Windows.
.PP
This extension is available to both, WebGL1 and WebGL2 contexts.
.RE
.SH CONSTANTS
The compressed texture formats are exposed by 4 constants and can be
used in two functions: \f[CR]compressedTexImage2D()\f[R] and
\f[CR]compressedTexSubImage2D()\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_RED_RGTC1_EXT\f[R]
Each 4x4 block of texels consists of 64 bits of unsigned red image data.
See also \c
.UR https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/direct3d10/d3d10-graphics-programming-guide-resources-block-compression#bc4
BC4 unsigned
.UE \c
\&.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RED_RGTC1_EXT\f[R]
Each 4x4 block of texels consists of 64 bits of signed red image data.
See also \c
.UR https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/direct3d10/d3d10-graphics-programming-guide-resources-block-compression#bc4
BC4 signed
.UE \c
\&.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_RED_GREEN_RGTC2_EXT\f[R]
Each 4x4 block of texels consists of 64 bits of compressed unsigned red
image data followed by 64 bits of compressed unsigned green image data.
See also \c
.UR https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/direct3d10/d3d10-graphics-programming-guide-resources-block-compression#bc5
BC5 unsigned
.UE \c
\&.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RED_GREEN_RGTC2_EXT\f[R]
Each 4x4 block of texels consists of 64 bits of compressed signed red
image data followed by 64 bits of compressed signed green image data.
See also \c
.UR https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/direct3d10/d3d10-graphics-programming-guide-resources-block-compression#bc5
BC5 signed
.UE \c
